  "title": "Netflix Q1 2025 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2025-04-15T20:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2025_Q1",
  "location": "Los Gatos, CA",
  "url": "https://ir.netflix.net/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "greg-peters",
      "speaker_name": "Greg Peters",
      "speaker_role": "Co-CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "Q1 2025 was a strong start to the year. We added 9.3 million paid subscribers to reach 301 million globally, crossing 300 million for the first time. Our advertising tier now has 40 million monthly active users, up from 23 million a year ago. Live sports content drove record single-day viewing in Q1 — our WWE Raw deal alone contributed 2.1 million incremental subscribers in the first month. We expect to cross 320 million subscribers by year-end."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "spencer-neumann",
      "speaker_name": "Spencer Neumann",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:18:00",
      "text": "Revenue was $10.5 billion, up 13% year-over-year. Operating income was $3.3 billion, with a 31.7% operating margin, up from 28.1% a year ago. Free cash flow was $2.9 billion. For Q2, we expect revenue of $10.4–10.8 billion and an operating margin of approximately 33%."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:36:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Mark Mahaney at Evercore ISI."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-mark-mahaney",
      "speaker_name": "Mark Mahaney",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:36:20",
      "text": "Greg, 40 million ad-tier MAUs — can you help us frame the ARPU uplift from the ad tier versus standard, and when you expect advertising to become a meaningful revenue contributor at say 10% or more of total?"
    }
  ],
